 Two persons were reported killed yesterday in the Alapata area of Ile-Ife and Modakeke in Osun State. It was learnt that youths from Modakeke discovered the bodies and alleged that they were killed by Ile-Ife people. The discovery of the bodies sparked tension in the two communities. Spokesman of Modakeke Progressive Union, Venerable Debo Babalola said they heard about the incident, but had no details. Also, police spokesperson Yemisi Opalola said, “We don’t have details of the incident but we are working on the matter.”